# {project} — conducted by Conductor

This project is enrolled in **Conductor**: development is conducted through an
11-gate, role-driven flow grounded in a library of reference books. The roles
below live as project-scoped Agents/Skills under `.claude/` and are loaded
automatically by Claude Code — no plugin required.

- **Type:** {type}
- **Stack:** see [`.cdt/stack/{type}.md`](.cdt/stack/{type}.md)
- **Roles:** the Agents in `.claude/agents/` with their Skills in
  `.claude/skills/` — a subset selected for this project type. Each Agent
  declares its own `model` (opus/sonnet/haiku); invoking it **as a subagent (Task
  tool)** runs it on that tier, overriding the session default.
- **Gates pause for you:** the flow **stops at every gate** to present its
  decisions + library citations and **ask your approval before advancing**
  (Gate protocol step 5). It does not run end-to-end unattended.
- **Entry point — run `/cdt <demand>`:** this slash command is the flow's
  control loop (recall → RAG → delegate to a subagent → record → your
  checkpoint). Driving a demand any other way leaves the flow as passive
  guidance, which a normal task prompt will bypass. Avoid pairing it with
  "run autonomously / commit each step" — that disables the per-gate checkpoint.

